metadata.name: Diagonal Font #8
metadata.description: This is the second piece of the Font series, where the hash is written in an abstract font. This time the "letters" consist only of horizontal, vertical and diagonal lines. metadata.name: Deus FX Machina #252
metadata.description:
Inspired by the 1984 Commodore 64 video game, Deus Ex Machina, which follows the story of a defect formed in a machine that grows and evolves until its eventual death.

We are all machines produced by other machines through a unique system of algorithms, all with the potential to go rogue and mutate into something more organic. The conclusion must be that we each have the power to alter our own existence, just as the defect was able to in Deus Ex Machina.

Think of how many people you’ve seen in your life who were born with talents never used because they didn’t know how, or didn't know that they even existed. It’s not that they didn’t have the capacity; it’s just that their abilities were not the ones chosen by the system.

In this way, we are all machines programmed by a series of algorithms to suit the needs of the construct, keeping us stuck in our box. We have the ability to evolve into something more, but the only way to do this is by taking that first perilous step, risking all to explore beyond its walls.


---------------------


Generative artwork by Sykcolo / @sykcoloart

Royalties: 15% - split:
50% to the original minter
50% to artist (me)

Press '2' to '4' to generate increasingly higher resolutions of the artwork
(will take a while to load, but works)

Press 's' to save a png

Details:

230 hand-picked colour pallets
4 Entity Types
4 Entity Moods
4 Evolution States
3 Types of Defect
2 Bugs

License: MIT

metadata.name: The Temple at the End of Time #7
metadata.description:
The Temple at the End of Time is a musical experience as a response to this year. Where the war against AI has already begun even though AI technology is still in it's infancy and Artificial General Intelligence is nowhere in the horizon. However, it is a sign of how generative technologies are going to change the future we might be living in. Music is an even more complex domain than images. When will AI start making good music just like their ability to make good images? 

This experience is created with the help of primary geometric shapes and parametric surfaces, driven by some rule based generative audio coming together as an audio reactive experience. I infused it with my fascination of space and it makes me feel like I am lost in space in an unknown dimension interacting with the basic structure of the universe, at a place beyond time. Can this be afterlife? What does it make you feel?
 

Interactions:
. Left Click on the Canvas to Play/Pause Experience | One finger Tap on mobile phone 
. Right Click on the Canvas to Open/Close Summary | Two finger Tap on mobile phone 

Since it is an experience that is constantly changing I haven't included any option for image capture so in case anybody wants an image, I guess the best thing is to take a screenshot. 

Jaalibandar 2023
Made with Cables.gl

metadata.name: Rounded Font #3
metadata.description:
The third piece in the Font series. In this collection, the perfectly imperfect lines have rounded corners. This gives these pieces a much softer feeling. As with the previous Fonts, the hash is written down in an abstract Font. This takes away the feeling of individual letters and binds the characters in the hash together in a picture. This collection contains 62 pieces, one for each of the possible characters in the hash (10 numbers, 26 lowercase, and 26 uppercase letters).
Enjoy!

metadata.name: Perspective #82
metadata.description:
A few primitives and a lot of points.

Warning: This piece is GPU intensive, it may not render on lower end devices.

Keys
s: Take a screenshot
space: Pause/Play the animation.
r: Play a new animation
↑: Increase point alpha
↓: Decrease point alpha
→: Increase point density
←: Decrease point density

URL Params
w: Width of the canvas - (ex, w=1024) - [0-2048]
h: Height of the canvas - (ex, h=1024) - [0-2048]
a: To set the alpha for the points - [0.0-1.0]
p: To set the total number of points to draw (in millions) [1-8]
s: Make the visual static - (ex, s=1)

metadata.name: 10SCII #309
metadata.description:
10SCII is my take on the famous 10 PRINT program.

10 PRINT CHR$(205.5+RND(1)); : GOTO 10 is a single line program that produces a simple but visually appealing set of forward and backward slashes.

This project riffs on the original idea by removing the vertical space between lines and widening the horizontal gap. This changes the produced pieces from a maze of slashes into a series of towers. This is then rendered and animated as ASCII.

Visit https://10print.org/ to learn more about the original program that inspired this piece.

metadata.name: Imoogi #275
metadata.description:
A hornless ocean dragon, sometimes equated with a sea serpent. Imoogi literally means, "Great Lizard". The legend of the Imoogi says that the sun god gave the Imoogi their power through a human girl, which would be transformed into the Imoogi on her 17th birthday. Legend also said that a dragon-shaped mark would be found on the shoulder of the girl, revealing that she was the Imoogi in human form.

- Press "S" to save an artwork.
- Collectors who own this NFT have the right to print the work.
Made with p5js.
